karn@unix.ka9q.ampr.org (Phil Karn) writes:

> But consider that even without a cryptographic module per se, DOS 6.0
> is really going to complicate life for law enforcement types who try
> to use Norton Utilities (or similar raw disk utilities) to search for
> "interesting" stuff that might be hidden on a seized computer's hard
> disk.

Uh, who knows... As somebody just posted to alt.security.pgp, wiping
files on compressed volumes might be much less secure, because the
image of the file filled with a single pattern usually compresses much
better and might leave "leftovers" on the compressed volume...

